stion', '', '', '2014-04-17 12:14:35', '2014-04-17 00:14:35', '', '0', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=56', '0', 'wpcf7_contact_form', '', '0'), ('57', '1', '2013-01-06 03:30:18', '2013-01-06 03:30:18', 'This is the submit page', 'Submit a Topic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-5', '', '', '2013-01-06 03:30:18', '2013-01-06 03:30:18', '', '5', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/5-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('58', '1', '2013-01-06 03:38:26', '2013-01-06 03:38:26', 'This is the submit page', 'Submit a Question', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-6', '', '', '2013-01-06 03:38:26', '2013-01-06 03:38:26', '', '5', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/5-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('415', '1', '2013-01-14 19:15:08', '2013-01-14 07:15:08', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-412\" alt=\"saveseven-screen6\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-409\" alt=\"saveseven-screen3\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-410\" alt=\"saveseven-screen4\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-411\" alt=\"saveseven-screen5\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-407\" alt=\"saveseven-screen1\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-408\" alt=\"saveseven-screen2\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>', 'Save Seven', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '413-revision-2', '', '', '2013-01-14 19:15:08', '2013-01-14 07:15:08', '', '413', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/413-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('416', '1', '2014-05-28 21:06:01', '2014-05-28 09:06:01', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users could watch the womens stories about breast cancer and leave comments\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-408\" alt=\"saveseven-screen2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could then choose friends to share the video with via facebook or email\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-410\" alt=\"saveseven-screen4\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could choose 7 women to share it with from facebook through my custom friend picker\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-411\" alt=\"saveseven-screen5\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The 7 women would then be displayed with their profile pictures\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-412\" alt=\"saveseven-screen6\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\n<h3>Goals</h3>\nThis project aimed to reach every woman in New Zealand with the message that early detection via breast screening is the best way to save the lives of the women we care about. The main driving force behind the online campaign was for users to watch the compelling stories of 7 quite different women who have beaten breast cancer and then share them on facebook with 7 women they care about.\n<h3>Technology</h3>\nThe main nav of the videos was built in flash while the rest of the site was built on top of the Zend Framework. The site uses the Youtube API for video events to trigger an overlay screen over the video. It also used the facebook API, Facebook Open Graph, JQuery and a bit of fancy HTML &amp; CSS.\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\nOne of the main challenges was to build a friend picker that deviated from the standard facebook functionality. We wanted to be able to only show the users friends who are listed as female on the facebook graph. We also wanted the  video to be posted the wall of the 7 women and make sure the audience is more relevant and also to help gain traction and visibility for the campaign.\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\nThe standard facebook friend picker was not enough, it only sends out app invites rather than wall posts and could not be customized to show different data sets. After we had app permissions granted to look at the users friends list, used FQL and the Facebook PHP API to query graph and return all the users friends listed as Female. From that data set I was able to look up those users facebook IDs on the Open Graph and get their Name, Profile Picture and used these to build the layout of the custom friend picker. Although it has a different color scheme, we tried to make it as close to the native facebook friend picker in terms of functionality. You could select up to 7 friends, then when the user clicked send the facebook app would post the video they selected on the site to all the women they had selected which could be watched straight on the facebook news feed along with a link to the site.\n<h3>Results</h3>\nSave Seven had a great core idea and a unique way of spreading its message. The friend picker ended up being such a hit that I packaged it up to be added to our code library for future projects and it has been re purposed many times since it was built. Its always great to try something you haven\'t done before, especially when it works great and is for a great cause.\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\nSave Seven won a Gold Axis for best Charity Campaign at the Axis Awards in 2012 and has won a few awards overseas as well.\n<h3>Live site</h3>\n<a title=\"Save Seven\" href=\"http://www.saveseven.co.nz\" target=\"_blank\">www.saveseven.co.nz</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Save Seven', 'Seven women every day are diagnosed with Breast Cancer in New Zealand. Our mission was to encourage people to reach out to seven women they care about and spread the message of how early detection saves lives. This a won Gold Axis for best Charity campaign of 2011 ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '413-autosave', '', '', '2014-05-28 21:06:01', '2014-05-28 09:06:01', '', '413', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/413-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('417', '1', '2013-01-14 19:15:23', '2013-01-14 07:15:23', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-412\" alt=\"saveseven-screen6\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen6-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-409\" alt=\"saveseven-screen3\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-410\" alt=\"saveseven-screen4\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-411\" alt=\"saveseven-screen5\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen5-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-407\" alt=\"saveseven-screen1\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-408\" alt=\"saveseven-screen2\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>', 'Save Seven', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '413-revision-3', '', '', '2013-01-14 19:15:23', '2013-01-14 07:15:23', '', '413', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/413-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('65', '1', '2013-01-06 04:52:47', '2013-01-06 04:52:47', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nunc ac aliquam orci. Praesent vitae tellus elit