\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339 \" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340 \" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341 \" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-9', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:31:21', '2013-01-12 09:31:21', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('348', '1', '2013-01-12 21:27:37', '2013-01-12 09:27:37', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338 \" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339 \" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340 \" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341 \" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-6', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:27:37', '2013-01-12 09:27:37', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('343', '1', '2013-01-12 21:19:57', '2013-01-12 09:19:57', '[caption id=\"attachment_338\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338\" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_339\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339\" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340\" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341\" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions[/caption]', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-2', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:19:57', '2013-01-12 09:19:57', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('344', '1', '2013-02-28 12:59:40', '2013-02-28 00:59:40', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338 \" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339 \" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340 \" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341 \" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\n<h3>Goals</h3>\nThis project aimed to create a Facebook app housed on the TVNZU page which allowed facebook users to watch the live show. It was to allow the users to get involved in the discussions the presenters were having and even get their comments to appear in real time on live TV. It was also to create a sense of community within the users friends by allowing them to invite their friends to watch the show and also display a list of which of your friends were currently tuned in via the app.\n<h3>Technology</h3>\nThis project was built on the Zend Framework and implements the Facebook API, JQuery, AJAX, a custom scroll bar JS library and of course HTML &amp; CSS.\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\nThe main challenge was that discussion feed needed to have the same user experience as Facebook but the feed functionality isn\'t part of the Facebook API and it needed to poll the server to add new comments without refreshing. The app also had to integrate with the users friends list and keep a track of who was online so we could display if any of your friends were watching and also have an invite mechanic. There was also the archiving of old discussions and polls as well as the feed moderation for the comments that went to air and CMS for the app.\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\nWe had to recreate the Facebook feed\'s functionality from scratch with the added ability to flag posts for moderator review. This became a very difficult task when there\'s so much integration. Every time we AJAX\'d in a new set of posts we had to bump the same number off the bottom so the pagination was intact while keeping their indexes for the likes and times all correct. We had to update the posts times, amount of likes and comment totals and then once everything was loaded, refresh the custom scroll bar height. The scroll lock button paused new comments from auto-updating which was also quite difficult to get working seamlessly.\n\nConnecting people with their friends was an important part of the app. We kept a database record of the Facebook ID\'s of everyone who logged into the app against a timestamp and if you\'d polled our server in the last 30 seconds we considered you to be in current use of the app. We then would look at the logged in users friends list and cross section that with the people who are currently logged in and display their profile picture and a link to their profile in a grid under the X Friends Watching heading. From here you could also invite your friends to watch the show through the Ulive app and this was done with the Facebook API\'s App Invite functionality.\n\nThe CMS was relatively straight forward, once a comment was approved to go to air it would be sent via a CURL request to an API at the TVNZ studio. This would then run through their system and be put up on the screen along with the users Name, Profile pic and Age which we got from their Facebook profile.\n<h3>Results</h3>\nThis project turned out to be a great piece of programming. The integration of so many technologies ended up seeming pretty smooth despite having to do a lot of bug fixing and tying up loose ends. Integrating a Facebook app with a live TV show was a first for me and actually a world wide first which caught the attention of a lot of people in technology sphere.\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\nThis app was featured on the Facebook developer blog and was also featured on quite a few online newspapers and blogs.\n<h3>Live site</h3>\n<a title=\"U Live\" href=\"https://apps.facebook.com/tvnz-ulive\" target=\"_blank\">https://apps.facebook.com/tvnz-ulive</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Ulive', 'This project encompassed a wide range of web technologies. It was the first facebook app to allow users to interact with live television and was featured on facebook\'s developer blog.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-autosave', '', '', '2013-02-28 12:59:40', '2013-02-28 00:59:40', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('625', '1', '2013-02-27 12:27:58', '2013-02-27 00:27:58', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338 \" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339 \" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340 \" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341 \" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nThis project aimed to create a Facebook app housed on the TVNZU page which allowed facebook users to watch the live show. It was to allow the users to get involved in the discussions the presenters were having and even get their comments to appear in real time on live TV. It was also to create a sense of community within the users friends by allowing them to invite their friends to watch the show and also display a list of which of your friends were currently tuned in via the app.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built on the Zend Framework and implements the Facebook API, JQuery, AJAX, a custom scroll bar JS library and of course HTML &amp; CSS.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nThe main challenge was that discussion feed needed to have the same user experience as Facebook but the feed functionality isn\'t part of the Facebook API and it needed to poll the server to add new comments without refreshing. The app also had to integrate with the users friends list and keep a track of who was online so we could display if any of your friends were watching and also have an invite mechanic. There was also the archiving of old discussions and polls as well as the feed moderation for the comments that went to air and CMS for the app.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nWe had to recreate the Facebook feed\'s functionality from scratch with the added ability to flag posts for moderator review. This became a very difficult task when there\'s so much integration. Every time we AJAX\'d in a new set of posts we had to bump the same number off the bottom so the pagination was intact while keeping their indexes for the likes and times all correct. We had to update the posts times, amount of likes and comment totals and then once everything was loaded, refresh the custom scroll bar height. The scroll lock button paused new comments from auto-updating which was also quite difficult to get working seamlessly.\r\n\r\nConnecting people with their friends was an important part of the app. We kept a database record of the Facebook ID\'s of everyone who logged into the app against a timestamp and if you\'d polled our server in the last 30 seconds we considered you to be in current use of the app. We then would look at the logged in users friends list and cross section that with the people who are currently logged in and display their profile picture and a link to their profile in a grid under the X Friends Watching heading. From here you could also invite your friends to watch the show through the Ulive app and this was done with the Facebook API\'s App Invite functionality.\r\n\r\nThe CMS was relatively straight forward, once a comment was approved to go to air it would be sent via a CURL request to an API at the TVNZ studio. This would then run through their system and be put up on the screen along with the users Name, Profile pic and Age which we got from their Facebook profile.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThis project turned out to be a great piece of programming. The integration of so many technologies ended up seeming pretty smooth despite having to do a lot of bug fixing and tying up loose ends. Integrating a Facebook app with a live TV show was a first for me and actually a world wide first which caught the attention of a lot of people in technology sphere.\r\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\r\nThis app was featured on the Facebook developer blog and was also featured on quite a few online newspapers and blogs.\r\n<h3>Additional</h3>\r\nThe site has undergone a design overhaul since we launched it back in 2010 but its still up and running: <a title=\"Ulive facebook app\" href=\"https://apps.facebook.com/tvnz-ulive/\" target=\"_blank\">https://apps.facebook.com/tvnz-ulive/</a>', 'Ulive', 'This project encompassed a wide range of web technologies. It was the first facebook app to allow users to interact with live television and was featured on facebook\'s developer blog.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-35', '', '', '2013-02-27 12:27:58', '2013-02-27 00:27:58', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-35/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('345', '1', '2013-01-12 21:20:14', '2013-01-12 09:20:14', '[caption id=\"attachment_338\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338\" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_339\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339\" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340\" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341\" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions[/caption]', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-3', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:20:14', '2013-01-12 09:20:14', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('347', '1', '2013-01-12 21:25:04', '2013-01-12 09:25:04', '<div class=\"gallery\">\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_338\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338 \" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_339\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339 \" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340 \" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a class=\"fancybox\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341 \" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions[/caption]\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-5', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:25:04', '2013-01-12 09:25:04', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('346', '1', '2013-01-12 21:23:25', '2013-01-12 09:23:25', '<div class=\"gallery\">\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_338\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-338\" alt=\"Ulive comments page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_339\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-339\" alt=\"Ulive voting page \" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_340\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-340\" alt=\"Ulive streaming page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_341\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-341\" alt=\"Ulive invite page\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a> Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions[/caption]\r\n</div>', 'Ulive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-4', '', '', '2013-01-12 21:23:25', '2013-01-12 09:23:25', '', '337', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/337-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('406', '1', '2013-01-14 19:12:49', '2013-01-14 07:12:49', '', 'saveseven-featured', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'saveseven-featured', '', '', '2013-01-14 19:12:49', '2013-01-14 07:12:49', '', '0', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/saveseven-featured.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('240', '1', '2013-01-07 22:47:35', '2013-01-07 10:47:35', 'This is a site dedicated to writing better code through sharing tricks and tips I\'ve learned along my journey. I\'ll be trying to cover a broad spectrum from the basics to the complex and everything in between.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nIf you have any specific problems that you\'d like me to cover in an article, feel free to drop me a message on the contact page.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nOr, head on over to the <a title=\"examples\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/examples/\">examples</a> section to check out some of my work.', 'Welcome to Geek Speak', 'Geek Speak is a site dedicated to writing better code through sharing tricks and tips.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'articles', '', '', '2013-08-13 17:14:22', '2013-08-13 05:14:22', '', '0', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/?page_id=240', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('241', '1', '2013-01-07 22:47:26', '2013-01-07 10:47:26', '', 'Articles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:47:26', '2013-01-07 10:47:26', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/240-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('242', '1', '2013-01-06 10:03:19', '2013-01-06 10:03:19', 'Vestibulum vel lorem nunc, in lobortis nunc. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. In cursus iaculis rutrum. Integer at sapien et velit porta euismod. Sed at libero ligula. Sed viverra porttitor nisl ut vulputate. Nam ac volutpat risus. Integer pretium libero a quam aliquet in auctor diam ultricies.\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"56\" title=\"Submit a Question\"]', 'Submit a Question', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-8', '', '', '2013-01-06 10:03:19', '2013-01-06 10:03:19', '', '5', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/5-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('243', '1', '2013-01-06 10:03:06', '2013-01-06 10:03:06', 'Vestibulum vel lorem nunc, in lobortis nunc. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. In cursus iaculis rutrum. Integer at sapien et velit porta euismod. Sed at libero ligula. Sed viverra porttitor nisl ut vulputate. Nam ac volutpat risus. Integer pretium libero a quam aliquet in auctor diam ultricies.', 'Portfolio', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-7', '', '', '2013-01-06 10:03:06', '2013-01-06 10:03:06', '', '6', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/6-revision-7/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('426', '1', '2013-01-16 18:22:11', '2013-01-16 06:22:11', '<div class=\"gallery\">\r\n<div class=\"topRow\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"By drinking Pepsi and redeeming codes, users could win a holiday with their mates\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-438\" alt=\"bromitment-screen1\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users allowed the facebook app and filled out their details to create a profile\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-439\" alt=\"bromitment-screen2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could then select 3 friends they wanted to take on the holiday through the custom friend picker\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen3.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-440\" alt=\"bromitment-screen3\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen3-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The picked friends would then be messaged on facebook to ask them to join\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen4.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-441\" alt=\"bromitment-screen4\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen4-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n<div class=\"bottomRow\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"All the users in the group could enter codes to boost their chances of winning\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen9.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-442\" alt=\"bromitment-screen9\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen9-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"If a user hadn\'t entered a code that day, the group leader could &quot;peer pressure&quot; them\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen10.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-443\" alt=\"bromitment-screen10\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen10-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users were &quot;peer pressured&quot; into entering codes by having one of our videos posted to their profile\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen11.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-444\" alt=\"bromitment-screen11\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen11-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The more codes your users entered per day gained you bonus entries\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen12.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-445\" alt=\"bromitment-screen12\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen12-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nPepsi Max Bromitment aimed to engage users to drink more Pepsi by getting users and their Bro\'s to make a commitment to each other. Teams were formed and entered product codes gave you points into the draw to win a holiday for you and your team.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in Flash with the API built on the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook API and AMF.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nThe main challenge here for me was building the API and integrating it with the flash front end and making the communication secure. The game seemed simple enough but there was a lot of hidden twists which made some of the logic quite difficult.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nWith smart class architecture I was able to minimize the amount of code written. Using a lot of smaller private functions rather than repeating code helped reduce the impact of functional changes or bug fixes. As with any competition, we encrypted the communication with a token so that it was much harder for someone to send requests directly to the API.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nBromitment was well executed from a design and development perspective, however I believe the mechanic itself was too convoluted for a lot of people to engage with.  It tried to take a pyramid scheme approach which meant that to be part of someone else\'s team, i have to create my own team with 3 other people. While this was supposed to help drive involvement i think it basically confused people as to where their codes were being applied and how the scheme worked.\r\n<h3>Notes</h3>\r\nThis was the the first full API I had written solo and despite not being hugely well received as a campaign, I was extremely happy with how the code ran.', 'Bromitment', 'Pepsi Max Bromitment aimed to engage users to drink more Pepsi by getting users and their Bro\'s to make a commitment to each other. Teams were formed and entered product codes gave you points into the draw to win a holiday for you and your team.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bromitment', '', '', '2014-05-28 22:24:28', '2014-05-28 10:24:28', '', '1004', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/?page_id=426', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('566', '1', '2013-02-27 12:22:06', '2013-02-27 00:22:06', '<div class=\"gallery\">\r\n<div class=\"topRow\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"By drinking Pepsi and redeeming codes, users could win a holiday with their mates\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen1.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-438\" alt=\"bromitment-screen1\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen1-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"Users allowed the facebook app and filled out their details to create a profile\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-439\" alt=\"bromitment-screen2\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could then select 3 friends they wanted to take on the holiday through the c