wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen11-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The more codes your users entered per day gained you bonus entries\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen12.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-445\" alt=\"bromitment-screen12\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bromitment-screen12-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nPepsi Max Bromitment aimed to engage users to drink more Pepsi by getting users and their Bro\'s to make a commitment to each other. Teams were formed and entered product codes gave you points into the draw to win a holiday for you and your team.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in Flash with the API built on the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook API and AMF.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nThe main challenge here for me was building the API and integrating it with the flash front end and making the communication secure. The game seemed simple enough but there was a lot of hidden twists which made some of the logic quite difficult.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nWith smart class architecture I was able to minimize the amount of code written. Using a lot of smaller private functions rather than repeating code helped reduce the impact of functional changes or bug fixes. As with any competition, we encrypted the communication with a token so that it was much harder for someone to send requests directly to the API.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nBromitment was well executed from a design and development perspective, however I believe the mechanic itself was too convoluted for a lot of people to engage with.  It tried to take a pyramid scheme approach which meant that to be part of someone else\'s team, i have to create my own team with 3 other people. While this was supposed to help drive involvement i think it basically confused people as to where their codes were being applied and how the scheme worked.', 'Bromitment', 'Pepsi Max Bromitment aimed to engage users to drink more Pepsi by getting users and their Bro\'s to make a commitment to each other. Teams were formed and entered product codes gave you points into the draw to win a holiday for you and your team.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '426-revision-13', '', '', '2013-02-27 12:22:06', '2013-02-27 00:22:06', '', '426', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/426-revision-13/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('246', '1', '2013-01-07 22:47:35', '2013-01-07 10:47:35', 'Test articles text', 'Articles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-2', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:47:35', '2013-01-07 10:47:35', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/240-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('247', '1', '2013-01-07 22:49:49', '2013-01-07 10:49:49', 'Test articles text', 'Articles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-3', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:49:49', '2013-01-07 10:49:49', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/240-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('248', '1', '2013-01-07 22:55:01', '2013-01-07 10:55:01', 'Test articles text', 'Welcome to Geek Speak', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-4', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:55:01', '2013-01-07 10:55:01', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/240-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('250', '1', '2013-01-07 22:58:45', '2013-01-07 10:58:45', 'Test articles text', 'Welcome to Geek Speak', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-6', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:58:45', '2013-01-07 10:58:45', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/240-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('249', '1', '2013-01-07 22:58:40', '2013-01-07 10:58:40', 'Test articles text', 'Welcome to Geek Speak test', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '240-revision-5', '', '', '2013-01-07 22:58:40', '2013-01-07 10:58:40', '', '240', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz