e table wasn\'t millions of rows long. All of these things combined with a queuing system allowed the server to tick over quite nicely despite the huge volume of traffic.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThis project was both simple and well executed. The core idea was great, it was easy to use, it was fun and the main goal of adopting dogs from the SPCA animal shelters exceeded expectation.\r\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\r\nThis site has won numerous awards including the Grand Axis, Gold Cannes, Spikes, Caples and many others. It was also featured on Campbell Live when it first launched.', 'BK Brand Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '454-revision-4', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:14:56', '2013-01-16 08:14:56', '', '454', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/454-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('465', '1', '2014-05-02 17:22:00', '2014-05-02 05:22:00', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The homepage has a custom slideshow gallery and all the content is manageable\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-459\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0003_Background\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The menu featured a custom accordion style menu with sub sections\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-458\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer 74\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The map can find you by GPS and show the nearest BK or you could search\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0001_screens_0006s_0011_Layer-75.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-457\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0001_screens_0006s_0011_Layer 75\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0001_screens_0006s_0011_Layer-75-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The contact form sends email directly to their customer service team\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0000_screens_0006s_0008_Layer-78.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-456\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0000_screens_0006s_0008_Layer 78\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0000_screens_0006s_0008_Layer-78-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\n<h3>Goals</h3>\nThis site was intended to give BK a more comprehensive online presence and bring their site up to date with some of the new web technologies.\n<h3>Technology</h3>\nThis project was built in HTML on top of the Zend Framework with a comprehensive Content Management System. It also implements the Google Maps API and JQuery.\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\nThe main challenge was the integration of the Google Maps into both the front end and the CMS. The Google Map had to show the user searched store locations and prioritize them in order of proximity to the user or the searched term.\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\nTo load the stores into the database I wrote a script to initialize the database entries automatically from an address list. This method worked with some but not all of the addresses, particularly those newer locations or ones in shopping complexes. We ended up coding a Google Map in the CMS which the admin could click on the map to record those latitude and longitude coordinates against that store. This proved to be the most useful way of getting the coordinates exact. Then using the latitude and longitude of the stores combined with either the users coordinates or the search terms coordinates we could use the Google Maps API to find the distance between the two points and then use that to order the returned results.\n<h3>Results</h3>\nThe BK Brand site is a solid piece of code which was put together both efficiently and well. Its cross compatible with all modern browsers and can even read the GPS coordinates if you\'re on a smart phone to show you your nearest stores. As far as a fast food brand site goes, this is definitely up the times.\n<h3>Live site</h3>\n<a title=\"BK Brand Site\" href=\"http://www.burgerking.co.nz\" target=\"_blank\">www.burgerking.co.nz</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'BK Brand Site', 'This site was intended to give BK a more comprehensive online presence and bring their site up to date with some of the new web technologies.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '454-autosave', '', '', '2014-05-02 17:22:00', '2014-05-02 05:22:00', '', '454', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/454-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('578', '1', '2013-02-27 12:29:08', '2013-02-27 00:29:08', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The homepage has a custom slideshow gallery and all the content is manageable\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-459\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0003_Background\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The menu featured a custom accordion style menu with sub sections\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-458\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer 74\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\