ny recent records as we could in memcache so that when the user shared their match, it could hopefully just get pulled from memory instead of the database. The other thing we did was archive matches more than 5 days old so that when we were doing a database look up the table wasn\'t millions of rows long. All of these things combined with a queuing system allowed the server to tick over quite nicely despite the huge volume of traffic.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThis project was both simple and well executed. The core idea was great, it was easy to use, it was fun and the main goal of adopting dogs from the SPCA animal shelters exceeded expectation.\r\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\r\nThis site has won numerous awards including the Grand Axis, Gold Cannes, Spikes, Caples and many others. It was also featured on Campbell Live when it first launched.', 'BK Brand Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '454-revision-8', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:21:09', '2013-01-16 08:21:09', '', '454', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/454-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('470', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:31', '2013-01-16 08:34:31', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The Facebook tab app has a like gate to unlock content for fans only\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-474\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer 2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could log into their V Republic account while still in Facebook\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-473\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer 88\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"If they didnt have an account they could register while still in Facebook too\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-472\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer 89\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They had to try and guess what flavor combinations the new V Blue was to win $10,000\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-471\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer 91\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nThis was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed the flavor correctly.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in HTML on top of the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook API and and is a Facebook App served inside a tab.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nThe competition needed to be restricted to people who like the V Energy Facebook page with what is known as a \"Like Gate\". The rest of the build was fairly simple as its simple just a form in a light box essentially. The form did however have to plug in to a Frucor\'s CRM database which was also worth noting.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nUsing the facebook API we were able to find out if the user likes the V Energy Page. If they like it, then we show the login screen, otherwise we show the lock screen. Once the user clicks the like button at the top of the tab, the page is forced to refresh by facebook which would reveal the login screen. The V CRM and the Database for the competition resided on different servers, so there was a bit of setup involved on the hosting side of things to allow database connections from different servers.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThe competition went really well with lots of user engagement. The facebook app was also considered such an easy and good format that it has been re skinned and re purposed multiple times since to run more competitions with.', 'V Blue Facebook Tab', 'This was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed what the flavor was. ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook-tab', '', '', '2014-05-28 22:24:06', '2014-05-28 10:24:06', '', '1004', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/?page_id=470', '0', 'page', '', '0'), ('471', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:18', '2013-01-16 08:34:18', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer 91', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_layer-91', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:18', '2013-01-16 08:34:18', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('472', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:19', '2013-01-16 08:34:19', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer 89', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_layer-89', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:19', '2013-01-16 08:34:19', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('473', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:19', '2013-01-16 08:34:19', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer 88', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_layer-88', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:19', '2013-01-16 08:34:19', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('474', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:20', '2013-01-16 08:34:20', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer 2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook_0003_layer-2', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:20', '2013-01-16 08:34:20', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('475', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:21', '2013-01-16 08:34:21', '', 'v-blue-facebook-featured', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'v-blue-facebook-featured', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:21', '2013-01-16 08:34:21', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook-featured.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('476', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:09', '2013-01-16 08:34:09', '', 'V Blue Facebook Tab', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '470-revision', '', '', '2013-01-16 20:34:09', '2013-01-16 08:34:09', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/470-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('477', '1', '2013-02-27 14:57:29', '2013-02-27 02:57:29', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The Facebook tab app has a like gate to unlock content for fans only\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-474\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer 2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could log into their V Republic account while still in Facebook\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-473\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer 88\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"If they didnt have an account they could register while still in Facebook too\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-472\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer 89\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They had to try and guess what flavor combinations the new V Blue was to win $10,000\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-471\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer 91\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\n<h3>Goals</h3>\nThis was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed the flavor correctly.\n<h3>Technology</h3>\nThis project was built in HTML on top of the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook API and and is a Facebook App served inside a tab.\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\nThe competition needed to be restricted to people who like the V Energy Facebook page with what is known as a \"Like Gate\". The rest of the build was fairly simple as its simple just a form in a light box essentially. The form did however have to plug in to a Frucor\'s CRM database which was also worth noting.\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\nUsing the facebook API we were able to find out if the user likes the V Energy Page. If they like it, then we show the login screen, otherwise we show the lock screen. Once the user clicks the like button at the top of the tab, the page is forced to refresh by facebook which would reveal the login screen. The V CRM and the Database for the competition resided on different servers, so there was a bit of setup involved on the hosting side of things to allow database connections from different servers.\n<h3>Results</h3>\nThe competition went really well with lots of user engagement. The APP was b\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\nThis site has won numerous awards including the Grand Axis, Gold Cannes, Spikes, Caples and many others. It was also featured on Campbell Live when it first launched.', 'V Blue Facebook Tab', 'This was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed what the flavor was. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '470-autosave', '', '', '2013-02-27 14:57:29', '2013-02-27 02:57:29', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/470-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('581', '1', '2013-02-27 14:49:25', '2013-02-27 02:49:25', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The Facebook tab app has a like gate to unlock content for fans only\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-474\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer 2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could log into their V Republic account while still in Facebook\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-473\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer 88\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"If they didnt have an account they could register while still in Facebook too\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-472\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer 89\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They had to try and guess what flavor combinations the new V Blue was to win $10,000\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-471\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer 91\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nThis was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed the flavor correctly.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in Flash with the CMS and API built on the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook and NEC APIs.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nA lot of the heavy lifting was left up to NEC. Their security grade facial recognition software which was accessed via an API handled the facial scanning and matching functionality. The main challenges for us was to capture the images, save them to the database and provide a URL for each result that could be shared on facebook with all the relevant meta data. The real challenge however arose after the build finished. The project went viral and was receiving over 100,000 hits per day. Streamlining the server side code and using better data access techniques to stop the database crashing under such a heavy load was quite technical.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nImages were first captured by the flash and sent to the server as a base64 image string. The PHP then used the GD library to merge the users image, the dogs image and the doggelganger logo onto a yellow background and resize it to become the image which would be shared by Facebook. We would also resize and save the user and dog images individually along with the NEC match statistics to be displayed on the share page.\r\n\r\nWhen the project went viral we had to implement a number of things to stop the server from crashing. We moved the flash file itself to an Amazon cloud servers so our web server didn\'t have to send it out every time it was requested. We found that the main bottleneck was around reading and writing to the database so we tried to limit the number of database calls to a minimum. We kept as many recent records as we could in memcache so that when the user shared their match, it could hopefully just get pulled from memory instead of the database. The other thing we did was archive matches more than 5 days old so that when we were doing a database look up the table wasn\'t millions of rows long. All of these things combined with a queuing system allowed the server to tick over quite nicely despite the huge volume of traffic.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThis project was both simple and well executed. The core idea was great, it was easy to use, it was fun and the main goal of adopting dogs from the SPCA animal shelters exceeded expectation.\r\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\r\nThis site has won numerous awards including the Grand Axis, Gold Cannes, Spikes, Caples and many others. It was also featured on Campbell Live when it first launched.', 'V Blue Facebook Tab', 'This was the facebook app product launch for the new blue flavor of V Energy drink. The main goal was to raise awareness of the new product by running a competition to give away $10,000 to anyone who guessed what the flavor was. ', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '470-revision-11', '', '', '2013-02-27 14:49:25', '2013-02-27 02:49:25', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/470-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('579', '1', '2013-02-27 08:41:02', '2013-02-26 20:41:02', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The Facebook tab app has a like gate to unlock content for fans only\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-474\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer 2\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0003_Layer-2-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They could log into their V Republic account while still in Facebook\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-473\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer 88\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0002_screens_0005s_0004_Layer-88-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"If they didnt have an account they could register while still in Facebook too\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-472\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer 89\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0001_screens_0005s_0003_Layer-89-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"They had to try and guess what flavor combinations the new V Blue was to win $10,000\" href=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-471\" alt=\"v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer 91\" src=\"http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/v-blue-facebook_0000_screens_0005s_0001_Layer-91-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nThis project aimed to create a website which users could upload their photo to and get their face matched to a dog which is up for adoption at the SPCA. The premise being that owners often look like their pets.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in Flash with the CMS and API built on the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook and NEC APIs.\r\n<h3>Challenges</h3>\r\nA lot of the heavy lifting was left up to NEC. Their security grade facial recognition software which was accessed via an API handled the facial scanning and matching functionality. The main challenges for us was to capture the images, save them to the database and provide a URL for each result that could be shared on facebook with all the relevant meta data. The real challenge however arose after the build finished. The project went viral and was receiving over 100,000 hits per day. Streamlining the server side code and using better data access techniques to stop the database crashing under such a heavy load was quite technical.\r\n<h3>Solutions</h3>\r\nImages were first captured by the flash and sent to the server as a base64 image string. The PHP then used the GD library to merge the users image, the dogs image and the doggelganger logo onto a yellow background and resize it to become the image which would be shared by Facebook. We would also resize and save the user and dog images individually along with the NEC match statistics to be displayed on the share page.\r\n\r\nWhen the project went viral we had to implement a number of things to stop the server from crashing. We moved the flash file itself to an Amazon cloud servers so our web server didn\'t have to send it out every time it was requested. We found that the main bottleneck was around reading and writing to the database so we tried to limit the number of database calls to a minimum. We kept as many recent records as we could in memcache so that when the user shared their match, it could hopefully just get pulled from memory instead of the database. The other thing we did was archive matches more than 5 days old so that when we were doing a database look up the table wasn\'t millions of rows long. All of these things combined with a queuing system allowed the server to tick over quite nicely despite the huge volume of traffic.\r\n<h3>Results</h3>\r\nThis project was both simple and well executed. The core idea was great, it was easy to use, it was fun and the main goal of adopting dogs from the SPCA animal shelters exceeded expectation.\r\n<h3>Recognition</h3>\r\nThis site has won numerous awards including the Grand Axis, Gold Cannes, Spikes, Caples and many others. It was also featured on Campbell Live when it first launched.', 'V Blue Facebook Tab', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '470-revision-9', '', '', '2013-02-27 08:41:02', '2013-02-26 20:41:02', '', '470', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/470-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('478', '1', '2013-01-16 20:34:31', '2013-01-16 08:34:31', '<div class=\"gallery\"><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The homepage has a custom slideshow gallery and all the content is manageable\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-459\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0003_Background\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0003_Background-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The menu featured a custom accordion style menu with sub sections\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-458\" alt=\"bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer 74\" src=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0002_screens_0006s_0012_Layer-74-200x200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a class=\"fancybox\" title=\"The map can find you by GPS and show the nearest BK or you could search\" href=\"http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bk-brandsite_0001_screens_0006s_0011_Layer-75.jpg\" rel=\"gallery1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-457\" alt=\"