2014-05-28 20:18:05', '2014-05-28 08:18:05', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0012_Layer-149.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('928', '1', '2014-05-28 20:18:10', '2014-05-28 08:18:10', '', 'Users could edit their facebook photos', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0013_layer-148', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:18:10', '2014-05-28 08:18:10', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0013_Layer-148.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('929', '1', '2014-05-28 20:18:16', '2014-05-28 08:18:16', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0014_Layer 147', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0014_layer-147', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:18:16', '2014-05-28 08:18:16', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0014_Layer-147.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('930', '1', '2014-05-28 20:20:50', '2014-05-28 08:20:50', '', 'The searchable gallery showed your friends at the top as well as the top 20', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0008_layer-154', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:20:50', '2014-05-28 08:20:50', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0008_Layer-154.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('934', '1', '2014-05-28 20:21:28', '2014-05-28 08:21:28', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0005_Layer 157', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0005_layer-157', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:21:28', '2014-05-28 08:21:28', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0005_Layer-157.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('935', '1', '2014-05-28 20:21:31', '2014-05-28 08:21:31', '', 'This is the video listing with voted state', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0006_layer-156', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:21:31', '2014-05-28 08:21:31', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0006_Layer-156.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('936', '1', '2014-05-28 20:21:36', '2014-05-28 08:21:36', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0007_Layer 155', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0007_layer-155', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:21:36', '2014-05-28 08:21:36', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0007_Layer-155.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('937', '1', '2014-05-28 20:10:32', '2014-05-28 08:10:32', '[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]', 'Holiday Replay', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-28', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:10:32', '2014-05-28 08:10:32', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-28/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('938', '1', '2014-05-28 20:35:04', '2014-05-28 08:35:04', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"929,928,927,926,925,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery ids=\"930,936,935,934,932,933,931\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-29', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:35:04', '2014-05-28 08:35:04', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-29/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('939', '1', '2014-05-28 20:36:35', '2014-05-28 08:36:35', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"929,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery ids=\"930,935,933,931\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-30', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:36:35', '2014-05-28 08:36:35', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-30/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('940', '1', '2014-05-28 20:37:37', '2014-05-28 08:37:37', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery ids=\"930,935,933,931\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-31', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:37:37', '2014-05-28 08:37:37', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-31/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('941', '1', '2014-05-28 20:42:01', '2014-05-28 08:42:01', '', 'The user could share the video to their wall and it would play in the timeline', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0004_layer-158-2', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:42:01', '2014-05-28 08:42:01', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0004_Layer-1581.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('942', '1', '2014-05-28 20:42:12', '2014-05-28 08:42:12', '', 'The user could then also share this video after watching it in the time line', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'portfolio-_0002s_0002_layer-160-2', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:42:12', '2014-05-28 08:42:12', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/portfolio-_0002s_0002_Layer-1601.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('943', '1', '2014-05-28 20:38:22', '2014-05-28 08:38:22', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"930,935,933,931\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-32', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:38:22', '2014-05-28 08:38:22', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-32/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('945', '1', '2014-05-28 20:46:02', '2014-05-28 08:46:02', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" columns=\"4\" ids=\"930,935,941,942\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-34', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:46:02', '2014-05-28 08:46:02', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-34/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('944', '1', '2014-05-28 20:42:23', '2014-05-28 08:42:23', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" columns=\"4\" ids=\"930,935,941,942\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-33', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:42:23', '2014-05-28 08:42:23', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-33/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('946', '1', '2014-05-28 20:46:57', '2014-05-28 08:46:57', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" columns=\"4\" ids=\"930,935,941,942\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 'Holiday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, I built the API behind it and guided the other two developers, ensuring their work pieced together into the final product.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '823-revision-35', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:46:57', '2014-05-28 08:46:57', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/articles/823-revision-35/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('947', '1', '2014-05-28 20:55:45', '2014-05-28 08:55:45', '', 'holiday-replay-featured', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'holiday-replay-featured', '', '', '2014-05-28 20:55:45', '2014-05-28 08:55:45', '', '823', 'http://www.geekspeak.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/holiday-replay-featured.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('948', '1', '2014-05-28 20:52:51', '2014-05-28 08:52:51', 'Holiday replay enabled people to connect with Facebook and write a story about how they lost cash while on holiday. We would then take their story and match the words up with keywords in our database which were mapped to images and video content that would be compiled along with any facebook photos found of that holiday, into a video sequence with the music track they selected.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"915,922,921,920,919,918,917,916\"]\r\n\r\nThey were able to review the images pulled from facebook for their story and remove any unwanted ones. They could then upload new ones from their facebook gallery or directly from their computer before submitting it to our gallery.\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"4\" link=\"file\" ids=\"928,927,926,924\"]\r\n\r\nTheir submitted stories ended up in a searchable gallery where they could be voted on. They could be shared on Facebook and even played within the time line until facebook removed SWF support from timeline posts.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"file\" columns=\"4\" ids=\"930,935,941,942\"]\r\n\r\nHoliday Replay was a unique project with a lot of technical aspects to work through. I was the lead developer on this project, guiding the other two developers and ensuring their work pieced together into the final product. I developed the back end of this application which consisted of all the API calls to get and save data along with a complex algorithm to figure out the users frame sequence.\r\n\r\nWe had a huge amount of manually compiled stock imagery which was linked to locations and key words. For example if you used the word \"taxi\" and your story was geo tagged as in New York, the background image of that frame would be the iconic yellow taxi of New York. However if it were geo tagged as being in London, you would get an image of their also iconic black taxi cabs.\r\n\r\nIf we couldn\'t match the word, we\'d pull media that was related to the geo tagged location. We\'d also look up any albums you had from that location and splice in some of your facebook images at appropriate intervals.\r\n\r\nEach frame was also assigned a custom font for the text, animation and static graphic to border the text.\r\n\r\nOne of the other developers took care of the front end of the site, while the third took care of compiling and animating the video sequence.\r\n\r\nBehind the scenes, this job was huge. It involved a custom API, facebook FQL queries, the Google Places API, Geo Coding, Canvas, HTML5 elements, Flash. The whole experience was mobile optimized to full functionality, you could submit, edit and watch the compiled video\'s all from your mobile phone or tablet.\r\n\r\nThe campaign performed well and has just come to a close. I\'ll update this post with some stats once they\'re available.', 'Holiday Replay', 